oc get configmap epaybridgetxn-config -n dev-bridge -o yaml | grep "context-path"

# in-pod: txn should now work
oc exec -n dev-bridge deploy/epaybridgetxn-epaylitebridgetxn -- \
  curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" localhost:8099/epaylite-bridge-txn-service/actuator/health
# expect 200

# through the gateway
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" https://dev.epay.sbi/epaylite-bridge-txn-service/actuator/health
# expect 200
```

One side note: your in-pod `txn` test returned `000 / exit code 7`, which means "connection refused" — likely the app was still booting in that 19-second-old pod when you ran it. Give it ~30–60s after restart before testing. The `txt` returning 404 (not 000) on the later run confirms the app was up by then and simply isn't serving `txn` yet — which the duplicate-line fix resolves.

So the root cause of "still not changed in cluster": the old `txt` line was never removed, so it overrode your new `txn` line. Remove it (via helm upgrade or oc edit), restart, and it'll work.
